coins.notes: Classic early American cent design. Large cents only (no small cents in this era).
coins.obverse_description: Liberty facing right with draped bust, hair tied with ribbon, 'LIBERTY' above, date below
coins.reverse_description: Wreath encircling 'ONE CENT', 'UNITED STATES OF AMERICA' around

coins.notes: Short-lived design by John Reich. Minting paused 1815-1816 due to copper shortage.
coins.obverse_description: Liberty facing left wearing cap, 'LIBERTY' on headband, stars around, date below
coins.reverse_description: Wreath encircling 'ONE CENT', 'UNITED STATES OF AMERICA' around

coins.notes: US copper cent minted 1793-1857. Multiple design types. Replaced by Flying Eagle Cent.
coins.obverse_description: Liberty head design (various types: Flowing Hair, Liberty Cap, Draped Bust, Classic Head, Coronet)
coins.reverse_description: Wreath design surrounding 'ONE CENT', 'UNITED STATES OF AMERICA'

coins.notes: Also known as Coronet or Matron Head. Large cent design 1816-1839.
coins.obverse_description: Liberty head with coronet inscribed 'LIBERTY', stars around, date below
coins.reverse_description: Wreath encircling 'ONE CENT', 'UNITED STATES OF AMERICA' around
